[White "2. Yugoslav Attack: Illustrative games"]
[Black "Alphonse Conrady vs. Dragoljub Velimirovic: Punishing a premature Bh6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 Bg7 4. Nc3 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nc6 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Bc4 O-O 8.
Bb3 d6 9. f3 Bd7 10. Qd2 Rc8 11. O-O-O Ne5 12. Bh6
{ A common mistake. In the Dragon, White should always be careful playing Bh6 if Black can meet it with ...Bxh6 Qxh6 ...Rxc3.   12.h4  h5  13.Bh6 ?!  also allows  13...Bxh6  14.Qxh6  Rxc3 }
12... Bxh6 13. Qxh6 Rxc3 14. bxc3 Qa5
{ Now Black gets the initiative and is objectively at least equal. } 15. Kb2
Rc8 16. Qe3 Qb6
{ 16...Qc5 !  is more aggressive: Black's queen is defended after ...a5-a4 so White does not have the resource of Nf5 with an endgame. }
17. Ka1 a5 18. Nf5 Qxe3 19. Nxe3 Rxc3
{ Black's compensation remains even in the endgame. Black can still pawn storm the queenside. }
20. Nd5 Nxd5 21. Bxd5 b5 { Black is slightly better and went on to win. } 22.
Kb2 b4 23. f4 Ng4 24. Rhe1 e6 25. Bb7 Ne3 26. Rxe3 Rxe3 27. Rxd6 Bb5 28. e5 a4
29. Rb6 a3+ 30. Kc1 b3 31. cxb3 Rc3+ 32. Kd2 Rxb3 33. axb3 a2 34. Rxb5 a1=Q 35.
Rb4 g5 36. fxg5 Qa5 37. Kc3 Qxe5+ 38. Kd3 Qc5 39. Rc4 Qb5 40. Bf3 Qxb3+ 41. Kd4
Kg7 42. h4 h6 43. gxh6+ Kxh6 44. h5 e5+ 45. Kc5 f5 46. Bd5 Qb8 *

