[White "2. Yugoslav Attack: Illustrative games"]
[Black "Bobby Fischer vs. Bent Larsen: Black plays ...Nxd4 with ...b5"]
[Result "*"]

{ This game way played in the 1958 Interzonal. } 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4
4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6
{ 'Larsen was one of the die-hards who refused to abandon the Dragon until recently. White's attack almost plays itself... weak players even beat grandmasters with it. I once thumbed through several issues of Shakhmatny Biulleten, when the Yugoslav Attack was making its debut and found the ratio was something like nine wins out of ten in White's favor.' - Bobby Fischer  (My 60 Memorable Games) }
6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 O-O 8. Qd2 Nc6 9. Bc4 Nxd4
{ Black wants to follow up with ...Be6. } 10. Bxd4 Be6 11. Bb3
{ 11.Bxe6 followed by 12.0-0-0 is also strong. } 11... Qa5 12. O-O-O b5 13. Kb1
b4
{ 13...Bxb3  14.cxb3 !  'Black cannot make any attacking headway against this particular pawn formation.' - Bobby Fischer }
14. Nd5 Bxd5
{ 14...Nxd5  15.Bxg7  Kxg7  16.exd5  Bd7  17.Rhe1  With a crushing bind.  Suetin-Korchnoi 1953. }
15. Bxd5
{ stronger is   15.exd5  Qb5  16.Rhe1  a5  17.Qe2 !  'when White abandons the attack and plays for pressure along the e-file instead' - Fischer.  Tal-Larsen, Zurich 1959 }
15... Rac8
{ Bd5 is too strong not to trade.   15...Nxd5  should equalize  16.exd5   16.Bxg7  Nc3+  17.Bxc3  bxc3  18.Qxc3  leads to a drawn rook endgame  16...Qxd5  with 17. Rhe1 or 17.Qxb4 with a dynamically balanced position }
16. Bb3
{ 'He won't get a second chance to snap off the bishop ! Now I felt the game was in the bag if I didn't botch it. I'd won dozens of skittles games in analogous postions and had it down to a science: pry open the h-file, sac, sac... mate !' - Fischer }
16... Rc7
{ Loses time, but prepares the advance of Black's a pawn.   16...Qb5 ?  17.Bxa7 }
17. h4 Qb5
{ 17...h5  18.g4 !  hxg4   18...Rfc8  19.Rdg1  19.h5  gives White a desicive attack. }
18. h5 { Not losing a tempo on g4. } 18... Rfc8
{ taking the h5 pawn loses by force.   18...Nxh5  19.Bxg7  Kxg7   19...Nxg7  20.Qh6  Nh5  21.g4  20.g4  Nf6  21.Qh6+  Kg8  22.g5  Nh5  23.Rxh5  gxh5  24.g6  with forced mate }
19. hxg6 hxg6 20. g4 a5 21. g5 Nh5 22. Rxh5
{ White sacrifices to blast open the kingside. } 22... gxh5
{ 22...a4  23.Rh7  and 23... Kxh7 loses to 24. Bxf7 } 23. g6
{ White's attack is desicive. } 23... e5 24. gxf7+ Kf8 25. Be3 d5 26. exd5 Rxf7
27. d6 Rf6 28. Bg5 Qb7 29. Bxf6 Bxf6 30. d7 Rd8 31. Qd6+ *

