[White "2. Yugoslav Attack: Illustrative games"]
[Black "Bobby Fischer vs. Edward Stepans: Black plays ...b5 without ...Nxd4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4
{ This game was played in the US Open in 1957. Bobby Fischer tied for 1st place with 10/12. }
1... c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 Nc6 7. f3 Bg7 8. Qd2
O-O 9. Bc4 a6
{ Too slow. Since White has a clear attacking plan  (castle queenside, open the h file, attack the kingside)  , Black should try to be faster to organize counterplay. 9...Bd7 10.0-0-0 Rc8 is more common. }
10. O-O-O Qc7 11. Bb3 b5
{ Loses material by force.   11...Nxd4  Black should usually take on d4 before playing ...b5. This is a common theme.  12.Bxd4  b5  Black didn't lose material yet but his counterattack is still too slow. White can pry open the h file with h4-h5  (g4 is optional)  and ...b4 can always be met with Nd5. }
12. Nxc6 Qxc6 13. Nd5
{ Threatening both 14. Nxf6+ Bxf6 15. Bd5 and 14. Nxe7. Black can't avoid losing material. }
13... Kh8
{ 13...Qe8  14.Nc7   13...Qd7  14.Nb6   13...Qb7  14.Nxf6+  Bxf6  15.Bd5 } 14.
Nxf6 e6 { White is winning. The rest is easy.   14...Bxf6  15.Bd5 } 15. Bh6 Bb7
16. Bxg7+ Kxg7 17. Ng4 f5 18. exf5 Rxf5 19. Qxd6 h5 20. Qe7+ Rf7 21. Qxf7+ Kxf7
22. Ne5+ Ke7 23. Nxc6+ Bxc6 24. Rhe1 Bd7 25. Rxd7+ *

