1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 Nc6
{ What if Black plays ...Nc6  (controlling the e5 square to impede e4-e5)  before castling with the intent of following up with ...d5? }
8. Qd2 d5 9. Bb5
{ White wins a pawn as ...Bd7 hangs the d5 pawn. Conclusion: ...d5 is unsound in the Dragon before Black plays ...Nc6 and ...0-0. }
