19. g5 Rb8+ 20. Kc1
{ White does not put his king on the dangerous dragon diagonal. White intends on playing exd5 next, and centralize with Rhe1. If Black plays ...Nd6  (after ...Ne8)  , White can pin the knight with Bf4 and either trade it or try to force matters with c5. }
