18. Rxh5 { Breakthrough! The simple 18.Nce2 intending Nxg3 is also good. }
18... gxh5 19. Rxg3 Ng6 20. Nf5
{ White has a powerful initiative and Black can't take on f5 because of Rxg6  (Bb3 pins the f7 pawn)  . White is also only down 2 pawns but he can immediately win the material back as he is threatening both the g7 bishop and the d6 pawn  (forking Black's rooks)  . }
