1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 O-O 8. Qd2
Nc6 9. Bc4 Bd7 10. O-O-O Rc8 11. Bb3 Ne5 12. Kb1 a6
{ 12...a6 is similar to 12...Re8. Black makes a waiting move that could be useful  (...a6 prepares ...b5)  without committing to ...Nc4 before White plays h4. Kb1 was a more useful waiting move than ...a6 and White can get a powerful attack with the thematic double pawn sacrifice. }
13. h4 h5 14. g4
{ 14.Bg5  is a good alternative, White can play  g4  later and has a superior version of the  12.h4  h5  13.Bg5  variation because Black wasted a tempo on  ...a6. }
14... hxg4 15. h5 { with Bh6 and Rdg1. } *

