[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 O-O 8. Qd2
Nc6 9. Bc4 Bd7 10. O-O-O Rc8 11. Bb3 Ne5 12. Kb1 a5
{ 12...a5 is inaccurate. White can close the queenside and shut down all of Black's counterplay. }
13. a4 Nc4
{ After 12...a5, this is Black's only method of trying to get active play. }
14. Bxc4 Rxc4 15. b3
{ Black has to retreat and White can follow up with 16. g4 17. h4 and 18. h5 with a powerful  (probably decisive)  attack. }
