24... Ra8 25. Kd2 Ra4 26. b3 Ra2 27. Rc1
{ White defended against Black's threats and is ready to continue moving his king to the kingside and fight for the initiative with g4 and f4-f5. White can consider giving up the c2 pawn with Ke2  allowing a tactic: ...Rxc2+ Rxc2 ...Bxc2 because Qxc2 loses to ...Qxd4  but it is okay to give back the extra pawn, white still has a kingside initiative. }
