[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6
{ The Accelerated Dragon. Black aims at delaying ...d6 in the hopes of playing ...d5 in one move. }
5. c4
{ The d5 square is under firm control. 5. c4 exposes the queenside, so White should castle kingside. }
5... Nf6 6. Nc3 Nxd4
{ Black trades a pair of knights and provokes White's queen to the center where it could be exposed. This avoids White's Nc2 setup, here we should choose something more aggressive to try to punish Black's early ...Nxd4.   in the main lines with  5...Bg7  6.Be3  Black usually delays  ...Nxd4  for a few moves and here White has not yet committed to  Be3 }
7. Qxd4 d6 { Preventing e5. } 8. Be2 Bg7 9. Bg5
{ Bg5 is well placed if White chooses an aggressive plan with f4 followed by f5 or e5. }
9... O-O 10. Qd2
{ Moving Qd4 off of the long diagonal. Discovered attacks could have become dangerous if White's queen remained on d4. }
10... a5 { Preparing ...a4. } 11. Rd1 { Preparing b3.   11.b3  Nxe4! } 11...
Be6 { 11...a4  12.e5! } 12. b3
{ White has more space and Black has no counterplay. White's plan is O-O followed by f4-f5 with a kingside initiative. }
