[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 a6
{ Black delays ...Bg7 in order to avoid being forced to castle or take on h6 after White takes on h6. This is the Accelerated Dragondorf. }
7. f3
{ Black is way behind on development. If he commits to delaying ...Bg7 and ...O-O, White should just develop rapidly and pawn storm the kingside. }
7... Nbd7
{ If Black plays ...b5 before White castles queenside, White should play a4 to open the queenside. }
8. Qd2 b5
{ If Black keeps making waiting moves then he will have a major development disadvantage, White could castle queenside and pawn storm  (g4-g5)  Black's kingside  (with or without Bc4)  . }
9. a4
{ White is better. If Black takes on a4 then he damages his pawn structure and helps White open the position.   9...b4  10.Na2  a5  11.c3  and the position opens up in White's favor }
